    <article id="Lec36">
        <header class="html-article-header">
            <h2><span class="html-lec-heading">Lecture 36: Intro to semantic Markup</span></h2>
        </header>
        <p class="sec-para-main">Semantic markup gives meaning to our HTML document so it makes more sense to the
            browser, assist screnreaders and boost SEO rating. For e.g People will
            understand if you made a div tag with class-nav but for browser it doesn't make much sense it still
            thinks
            that it is div with a class, it isn't able to identify that this is used to indicate that this is a
            navigation bar. To make our elements make sense to browser, we use semantic elements. A browser may not
            be
            able to identify that a div with class <mark>nav</mark> is a navigation bar but when you use <code
                class="html-tags">&ltnav></code> tag then it becomes clear to browser that you are trying to
            indicate
            that it is a navigation bar.</p>
    </article>
